# .droid-shield-allowlist
# Droid-Shield pre-push secret scanner — false-positive suppressions.
#
# Each line is a pattern (substring or regex) that the scanner should
# ignore when evaluating potential secret leaks. Only add patterns that
# have been confirmed to be benign by a code reviewer.
#
# Context: TL-9 (PLAN_IMPROVEMENT.md Phase 5)
# The scanner incorrectly flags the following as secret tokens:
#   • `tokens5h`  — a variable name in server.js / app.js / lib/rtk-metrics.js
#   • `tokens`    — generic JS identifiers in the codebase
#   • bare `0`    — default numeric values flagged as "token = 0"
#
# The false-positive logic is: the scanner treats any value that looks like
# a random-length alphanumeric string after "token" (including variable
# suffixes like "5h", "Weekly") as a credential. These are not credentials.

# Allowlisted false-positive patterns
tokens5h
tokensWeekly
savedTokens
inputTokens
outputTokens
cachedTokens
totalTokens
